All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
AbstractGameConnection
A general abstract class to implement methods not specific to a game connection.
AbstractGameConnectionClient
Abstract class to define the protected methods necessary for a game connection client.
AbstractGameConnectionServer<K>
Abstract class to define the protected methods necessary for a game connection server.
AbstractInputAction
AbstractInputAction is the base class from which all TAGE input actions are derived.
Angle
An angle is the figure formed by two rays sharing the same vertex end point and represents a measurement of the amount of rotation between them.
AnimatedShape
AnimatedShape contains functions for loading animated models, building animated shapes and their skeletons, and applying animations to the models at runtime.
AnimatedShape.EndType
Specifies what happens when reaching the end of an animation.
AnimatedSkeleton
A Skeleton describes the hierarchy and structure of any number of bones.
Animation
An Animation describes a sequence of frames that can be applied to an AnimatedSkeleton object.
AudioEar
This class acts as the abstract base class from which all concrete Audio Ears are derived.
AudioFormat
The format (file type) of the sound file.
AudioManager
This class acts as the abstract base class from which all concrete Audio Managers are derived.
AudioManagerFactory
This class is a Factory for creating audio manager objects -- that is, objects which implement the IAudioManager interface.
AudioPlayer
This class acts as the abstract base class from which all concrete Audio Players are derived.
AudioResource
This class represents an audio resource in memory.
AudioResourceType
The type of audio resource of the sound file.
BehaviorTree
BehaviorTree is a class that allows for the easy construction of a Beahvior Tree which is a technique used for creating Artificial Intelligence in video games.
BTAction
BTAction represents an action behavior node in a behavior tree.
BTBehavior
BTBehavior is an abstract base class that represents a node in a behavior tree.
BTComposite
A BTComposite node is an inner node that maintains a collection of BTBehavior child nodes.
BTCompositeType
BTCompositeType is an enumeration that contains the different types of composite nodes that exist.
BTCondition
A BTCondition node is a leaf node that performs a boolean check on read-only data gathered from the game world.
BTDecorator
BTDecorator is an abstract behavior node that contains a single BTBehavior child.
BTNodeType
BTNodeType is an enumeration that contains the different types of behavior nodes that exist.
BTRepeat
BTRepeat is a BTDecorator node that processes its child nodes a specific number of times before returning a return status.
BTSelector
A BTSelector node is a BTComposite that executes its child nodes from left to right looking for first success.
BTSequence
A BTSequence node is a BTComposite that executes its child nodes from left to right.
BTStatus
BTStatus is an enumeration that contains the different values of and valid states for a behavior's return status.
Camera
A Camera specifies the rendering viewpoint for a Viewport.
ComponentStateInfo
ComponentStateInfo stores state information for a specific component (key, button, or axis).
Cube
A Cube has 36 vertices, winding order CW, and texture coordinate from (0,0) to (1,1) on each side.
Degreef
An immutable single-precision floating point representation of an Angle, measured in degrees.
DisplaySettingsDialog
This class provides a dialog box for specifying display settings.
Engine
The Engine object holds references to the primary game engine components, and provides accessors for them.
GameConnectionClient
Concrete implementation of the client side for a game connection protocol.
GameConnectionServer<K>
A concrete implementation of a game server.
GameObject
GameObject holds the data associated with a node in the scenegraph.
HUDmanager
Manages up to two HUD strings, implemented as GLUT strings.
IAction
This interface specifies the methods which must be implemented by all concrete subclasses of AbstractInputAction.
IAudioEar
The IAudioEar interface exposes the public methods that all audio ears must implement.
IAudioManager
The IAudioManager interface exposes the public methods that all audio managers must implement.
IAudioPlayer
The IAudioPlayer interface exposes the public methods that all audio players must implement.
IClientInfo
General data structure to store client information necessary to implement the IClientInfo.sendPacket(Serializable).
IClientSocket
Defines a client side socket responsible for sending an receiving packets for the client side of a game.
IGameConnection
A general interface for game connections.
IGameConnection.ProtocolType
Enum for specifying the protocol type to be used in the network communications.
IGameConnectionClient
Defines a game connection client.
IGameConnectionServer
Defines the server side for a game.
IInputManager
This interface specifies the functions provided by an input manager implementation, independent of what underlying input package the input manager uses.
IInputManager.INPUT_ACTION_TYPE
INPUT_ACTION_TYPE enumerates the possible manners in which an IAction associated with a button or key will be invoked when the button or key generates an input event.
ImportedModel
Supports importing OBJ model files into the game.
InputManager
This class implements the IInputManager interface and acts as the central management point for all input devices available for controlling a game.
IServerSocket
Defines a server side socket.
